DESCRIPTION:Unit 1 Progress\n\nIcon Progress Bar/Navigation (built in brows
 er\, hidden in app)\n\n \n\n---------\nOBJECTIVE\n---------\n\nPractice a
 cquiring data programmatically using an API.\n\n------------\nINSTRUCTIONS
 \n------------\n\n* Choose a public API (e.g.\, OpenWeatherMap\, NASA API\
 , or a financial data API).\n\n* Write a Python script to send a request t
 o the API and retrieve data (e.g.\, current weather data for a specific ci
 ty\, recent astronomical data\, or stock prices).\n\n* Parse the JSON resp
 onse and save the relevant data into a CSV file.\n\n* Save this python fil
 e\, as we will extend this activity in the future.\n\n* Provide a brief de
 scription of the API and the data you retrieved.\n\n* Submit a pdf which i
 ncludes the following two items: a brief description of the API and data y
 ou retrieved and a screenshot of your of your code / CSV data (this can be
  partial\, just give us an idea of your work).\n\nNote: These activities a
 re meant to take 1-2 hours. If you find yourself spending much more time t
 han this please come to office hours for help\, take a break\, or search f
 or resources online.
