 _heading kl_panel_0">Database Acquisition (OPTIONAL for Advanced Users)</h
 3>\n<ul>\n<li>Load the <a class="instructure_file_link inline_disabled" ti
 tle="employees.db" href="https://elearning.mines.edu/courses/76742/files/8
 063744?wrap=1" target="_blank" data-api-endpoint="https://elearning.mines.
 edu/api/v1/courses/76742/files/8063744" data-api-returntype="File">employe
 es.db</a> in using pandas read_sql() function and store in a dataframe</li
 >\n<li>Print the dataframe's first few elements using the<span>&nbsp\;</sp
 an><code>.head()</code><span>&nbsp\;</span>command to see what data you ha
 ve</li>\n<li>Perform SQL queries to find the following information:<br>\n<
 ul>\n<li>Number of unique departments</li>\n<li>Average salary</li>\n<li>N
 umber of employees</li>\n<li>Who are the employees in the engineering depa
 rtment?</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h3>Par
 t 2: Unstructured Data</h3>\n<p>Data can be provided in various formats\, 
 with some examples beyond structured data being:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Sometimes\
 , you may need to access data held by another company. The best approach i
 s to use an API to request the company's data services\, which will return
  the necessary data.</li>\n<li>Sometimes\, you may need to work with an en
 tire directory of files. The best approach is to loop through the director
 y and read each file.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>TASK: </strong>Your task is 
 to practice using an API and reading a directory of text files to extract 
 information. Detailed instructions for each method are provided below.</p>
 \n<div id="kl_wrapper_3" class="kl_wrapper">\n<div id="kl_panel_block_0" c
 lass="">\n<div class="kl_panels_wrapper kl_panels_tabs">\n<h3 id="kl_panel
 _4" class="kl_panel_heading kl_panel_4">APIs</h3>\n<div id="kl_panel_4_con
 tent" class="kl_panel_content kl_panel_4">\n<h3 class="kl_panel_heading kl
 _panel_0">Application Programming Interfaces (mini project)</h3>\n<p><span
 >We will practice c</span>onnecting to the SpaceX API&nbsp\;<span>and see 
 what information we can get back!</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Connect to
  the SpaceX API</strong> - Set up a connection to the SpaceX API. We can u
 se the requests library to connect to the SpaceX API by specifying the API
  endpoint URL.<br>More info at: <a href="https://docs.spacexdata.com/" tar
 get="_blank">https://docs.spacexdata.com/</a>&nbsp\;</li>\n<li><strong>Ret
 rieve Data on Past Launches</strong> - Fetch data on past launches from th
 e SpaceX API. We can use the requests.get() method to send a GET request t
 o the SpaceX API endpoint and use the .json() method to parse the response
 .</li>\n<li><strong>Load Data into a Pandas DataFrame</strong> - Load the 
 retrieved data into a Pandas DataFrame.</li>\n<li><strong>Perform Basic Da
 ta Analysis</strong> - Perform basic data analysis on the retrieved data. 
 We can use the describe() and info() methods to get basic statistics and i
 nformation about the DataFrame.</li>\n<li><strong>Filter Data Based on Lau
 nch Success</strong> - Filter the data to find only successful launches. W
 e can use boolean indexing to filter the DataFrame for rows where the succ
 ess column is True.</li>\n<li><strong>Group Data by Year</strong> - <stron
 g>Note\,</strong> <strong>use the column "date_utc"</strong> in your datas
 et. Group the data by year and count the number of launches each year. We 
 can use the pd.to_datetime() method to convert the date column to datetime
 \, extract the year using the .dt.year accessor\, and use the groupby() me
 thod to group the data by year and count the number of launches.</li>\n</u
 l>\n</div>\n<h3 id="kl_panel_5" class="kl_panel_heading kl_panel_5">Direct
 ory of Files</h3>\n<div id="kl_panel_5_content" class="kl_panel_content kl
 _panel_5">\n<h3 class="kl_panel_heading kl_panel_5">Reading a Directory of
  Files</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Since we did not cover this\, you will be provided 
 the code to process of working with a directory of data. We will use a col
 lection of text data (movie reviews) to demonstrate how to load\, process\
 , and analyze unstructured text data.</li>\n<li><strong>Load Text Data fro
 m Files</strong> - See if you can setup the 'reviews' directory and read t
 he three given text files (e.g.\, <a class="instructure_file_link instruct
 ure_scribd_file inline_disabled" title="review1.txt" href="https://elearni
 ng.mines.edu/courses/76742/files/8063812?wrap=1" target="_blank" data-api-
 endpoint="https://elearning.mines.edu/api/v1/courses/76742/files/8063812" 
 data-api-returntype="File">review1.txt</a>\, <a class="instructure_file_li
 nk instructure_scribd_file inline_disabled" title="review2.txt" href="http
 s://elearning.mines.edu/courses/76742/files/8063901?wrap=1" target="_blank
 " data-api-endpoint="https://elearning.mines.edu/api/v1/courses/76742/file
 s/8063901" data-api-returntype="File">review2.txt</a>\, <a class="instruct
 ure_file_link instructure_scribd_file inline_disabled" title="review3.txt"
  href="https://elearning.mines.edu/courses/76742/files/8063926?wrap=1" tar
 get="_blank" data-api-endpoint="https://elearning.mines.edu/api/v1/courses
 /76742/files/8063926" data-api-returntype="File">review3.txt</a>). To load
  the data\, we have to use typical python file loading.\n<ul>\n<li>We will
  need the os package and have to loop through our files to find all .txt f
 iles.</li>\n<li>Once we find them\, we will load them into an array for st
 orage.</li>\n<li>And print them out to make sure we got all the files!</li
 >\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>As a stretch goal\, modify the code and see if you ca
 n read other types of files.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n
 <hr style="color: #92a2bd\; border: 1px solid\;">\n<h2 class="p1">SUBMITTI
 NG YOUR SOLUTION</h2>\n<p class="p1">Submit your notebook file. To submit 
 your notebook\, first clear all the cells (this won't matter too much this
  time\, but for larger data sets in the future\, it will make the file sma
 ller). Then use the File-&gt\;Download As-&gt\;Notebook to obtain the note
 book file. Finally\, submit the notebook file(s) with your solutions to Ca
 nvas.</p><script src="https://instructure-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account
 _98020000000000001/attachments/7108467/dp_app%20%25281%2529.js"></script>
END:VEVENT
