DESCRIPTION:---------------------------------------------------------\nOn t
 o classification\, and right into logistic regression!\n------------------
 ---------------------------------------\n\nIn 560\, you have explored and 
 applied a lot of powerful techniques for settings where your response vari
 able was quantitative. In settings where your response variable is qualita
 tive\, you need different tools\, so called classification methods\, and l
 ogistic regression is the main stay of all of them! Here you will get a ch
 ance to discuss the mathematical foundations and their implications for yo
 ur work in some depth.\n\n* What is the defining characteristic of a class
 ification problem?\n\n* Recall and explain what the issues are with using 
 a standard linear model to use for modeling a classification problem.\n\n*
  How does the logistical regression model differ from the linear regressio
 n model? How do you interpret the logistic regression predictions and the 
 inferred parameters?\n\n* Can cross-validation still be performed when we 
 are dealing with a classification problem? Why or why not?\n\n* Provide on
 e example application of a classification problem in a field of your choic
 e\, and discuss why a regression model is a poor fit in your example.\n\n
  \n\nPost your thoughts to the questions above and provide constructive f
 eedback to at least two (2) of your peers.\n\nYou will in turn receive fee
 dback from your colleagues and instructors\, and have until EOD Sunday to 
 address the feedback you receive from your colleagues and instructors befo
 re your discussion post will be graded.\n\nEstimated time requirement: 3 h
 ours
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Module 3 | Discussion [Fall 2025.MATH561A.81045]
URL;VALUE=URI:https://elearning.mines.edu/calendar?include_contexts=course_
 75552&month=09&year=2025#assignment_506608
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://instructu
 re-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account_98020000000000001/attachments/7108468/
 dp_app3.css"><h2>On to classification\, and right into logistic regression
 !</h2>\n<p>In 560\, you have explored and applied a lot of powerful techni
 ques for settings where your response variable was quantitative. In settin
 gs where your response variable is qualitative\, you need different tools\
 , so called classification methods\, and logistic regression is the main s
 tay of all of them! Here you will get a chance to discuss the mathematical
  foundations and their implications for your work in some depth.</p>\n<ul>
 \n<li>What is the defining characteristic of a classification problem?</li
 >\n<li>Recall and explain what the issues are with using a standard linear
  model to use for modeling a classification problem.</li>\n<li>How does th
 e logistical regression model differ from the linear regression model? How
  do you interpret the logistic regression predictions and the inferred par
 ameters?</li>\n<li>Can cross-validation still be performed when we are dea
 ling with a classification problem? Why or why not?</li>\n<li>Provide one 
 example application of a classification problem in a field of your choice\
 , and discuss why a regression model is a poor fit in your example.</li>\n
 </ul>\n<p>&nbsp\;</p>\n<p>Post your thoughts to the questions above and pr
 ovide constructive feedback to at least two (2) of your peers.</p>\n<p>You
  will in turn receive feedback from your colleagues and instructors\, and 
 have until EOD Sunday to address the feedback you receive from your collea
 gues and instructors before your discussion post will be graded.</p>\n<p><
 strong>Estimated time requirement: 3 hours</strong></p><script src="https:
 //instructure-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account_98020000000000001/attachmen
 ts/7108467/dp_app%20%25281%2529.js"></script>
END:VEVENT
