DESCRIPTION:Note: From module #3 onward your homeworks are done in teams of
  two. The randomly assigned group leader is in charge of submitting your j
 oint work\, which represents both of your consensus solution. We make this
  arrangement purposefully as a large part of being a great data scientist 
 involves good communication and technical exchange with colleagues to look
  at a problem from different view points and jointly decide on the solutio
 n approach. So make sure you communicate with your teammate and collaborat
 e on the homework. Let us know if you have any questions!\n\n \n\nHomewor
 k from Chapter 4.8 Exercises\n\n* Conceptual problems: 6ab\, 7\, 13a-d\, 1
 4abcf\n\nThrough this homework you will acquire the skill to perform logis
 tic regression\, which is a type of regression used to estimate the probab
 ility of an event. You also apply logistic regression to datasets containi
 ng economic data and gas mileage\, which you will later return to in the n
 ext module.\n\nUse any typesetting software of your choice for the concept
 ual questions and use R for all your analysis.\n\nEstimated time to comple
 te: 5:30 hours
