DESCRIPTION:Unit 2 Progress\n\nIcon Progress Bar/Navigation (built in brows
 er\, hidden in app)\n\n \n\n----\nTASK\n----\n\nYour task for this discus
 sion is to read the Introducing Scikit-Learn (specifically the Data Repres
 entation in Scikit-Learn) section in our Python Data Science Handbook. You
  will then post a discussion and a reply below! \n\nReminder: The book is
  a reference guide and we have assigned the above section as a reading on 
 this topic at a high-level. Keep in mind\, it contains much more informati
 on than we cover in our course. As time permits\, you may find some intere
 sting "extra" readings\, examples\, and information.\n\n------------------
 -----\nDISCUSSION REQUIREMENTS\n-----------------------\n\nOnce you have c
 ompleted this weeks reading\, you are asked to complete the following tas
 ks:\n\n* Post a 1-2 sentence response from the reading for 2 of the 3 belo
 w prompts:\n\n* The book section discusses the Features Matrix\, by conven
 tion\, what is this variable normally named (denoted as?) And\, provide yo
 ur understanding of what data would be stored in such a structure. \n\n* 
 The book section discusses the Target Array\, by convention\, what is this
  variable normally named (denoted as?) And\, provide your understanding of
  what data would be stored in such a structure.\n\n* Provide a free respon
 se: this can be anything from clarification questions\, something that piq
 ued your interest\, or maybe a personal experience you have with what was 
 discussed in the book section.\n\n* Post a meaningful reply to another stu
 dent's question/post. \n\nOur goal is to help you get a deeper understand
 ing of data science and discussions are a wonderful way to do this! Think 
 of this as a learning opportunity for both you\, your classmates\, and you
 r professor! Be sure to use academic language and question ideas from the 
 readings for clarity or to push your own thinking.  You may of course res
 pond to more than two of the questions and more of your classmates if you 
 would like.\n\n-------\nGRADING\n-------\n\nThis assignment is worth a tot
 al of 15 points this is split into 10 points for a thoughtful post and 5 p
 oints for a thoughtful reply.  Once you post your answers to your select
 ed questions\, you will be able to see your peer's responses. This discuss
 ion requires you to post first before seeing other responses. To see the s
 pecific grading criteria for this assignment\, please [view the discussio
 n rubric] (https://community.canvaslms.com/docs/DOC-10577-4212540120).
