DESCRIPTION:Unit 2 Progress\n\nIcon Progress Bar/Navigation (built in brows
 er\, hidden in app)\n\n \n\n----\nTASK\n----\n\nYour task for this discus
 sion is to read the Feature Engineering section in our Python Data Science
  Handbook. You will then post a discussion and a reply below!\n\nNote: we 
 will study the Introduction and Fundamentals of Machine Learning in the ne
 xt unit to tie all the concepts together and put all of this data acquisit
 ion and pre-processing into practice. \n\nReminder: The book is a referen
 ce guide and we have assigned the above section as a reading on this topic
  at a high-level. Keep in mind\, it contains much more information than we
  cover in our course. As time permits\, you may find some interesting "ext
 ra" readings\, examples\, and information.\n\n-----------------------\nDIS
 CUSSION REQUIREMENTS\n-----------------------\n\nOnce you have completed t
 his weeks reading\, you are asked to complete the following tasks:\n\n* P
 ost a 1-2 sentence response from the reading for 2 of the 3 below prompts:
 \n\n* The book section discusses several "common needs" or "types" of feat
 ure engineering\, select one that resonates with your interests\, study it
  further\, then provide a few sentences about what it is and a common meth
 od to address it. \n\n* The Imputation of Missing data is discussed in de
 tail and the book mentions there are sophisticated approaches beyond what 
 is covered\; what are the common or baseline imputation methods listed and
  discuss why would we need such an approach?\n\n* Provide a free response:
  this can be anything from clarification questions\, something that piqued
  your interest\, or maybe a personal experience you have with what was dis
 cussed in the book section.\n\n* Post a meaningful reply to another studen
 t's question/post. \n\nOur goal is to help you get a deeper understanding
  of data science and discussions are a wonderful way to do this! Think of 
 this as a learning opportunity for both you\, your classmates\, and your p
 rofessor! Be sure to use academic language and question ideas from the rea
 dings for clarity or to push your own thinking.  You may of course respon
 d to more than two of the questions and more of your classmates if you wou
 ld like.\n\n-------\nGRADING\n-------\n\nThis assignment is worth a total 
 of 15 points this is split into 10 points for a thoughtful post and 5 poin
 ts for a thoughtful reply.  Once you post your answers to your selected 
 questions\, you will be able to see your peer's responses. This discussion
  requires you to post first before seeing other responses. To see the spec
 ific grading criteria for this assignment\, please [view the discussion r
 ubric] (https://community.canvaslms.com/docs/DOC-10577-4212540120).
