DESCRIPTION:Unit 2 Progress\n\nIcon Progress Bar/Navigation (built in brows
 er\, hidden in app)\n\n \n\n----\nTASK\n----\n\nYour task for this discus
 sion is to read the In Depth: Principal Component Analysis section in our 
 Python Data Science Handbook. You will then post a discussion and a reply 
 below! \n\nNote: we will study the Introduction and Fundamentals of Mach
 ine Learning in the next unit to tie all the concepts together and put all
  of this data acquisition and pre-processing into practice. Please focus o
 n the overview of PCA.\n\nReminder: The book is a reference guide and we h
 ave assigned the above section as a reading on this topic at a high-level.
  Keep in mind\, it contains much more information than we cover in our cou
 rse. As time permits\, you may find some interesting "extra" readings\, ex
 amples\, and information.\n\n-----------------------\nDISCUSSION REQUIREME
 NTS\n-----------------------\n\nOnce you have completed this weeks reading
 \, you are asked to complete the following tasks:\n\n* Post a 1-2 sentenc
 e response from the reading for 2 of the 3 below prompts:\n\n* The book se
 ction discusses how PCA can be used for dimensionality reduction\, discuss
  your understanding of what is involved in the application of PCA to a dat
 aset\, how does this affect the relationship between the data points\, and
  what can the result be used for?\n\n* Review the section Choosing the Num
 ber Components\, discuss what the principal components are and how you can
  use explained variance ratio to estimate how many components are ned to d
 escribe close to 100% of the variance.\n\n* Provide a free response: this 
 can be anything from clarification questions\, something that piqued your 
 interest\, or may be a personal experience you have with what was discusse
 d in the book section.\n\n* Post a meaningful reply to another student's q
 uestion/post. \n\nOur goal is to help you get a deeper understanding of d
 ata science and discussions are a wonderful way to do this! Think of this 
 as a learning opportunity for both you\, your classmates\, and your profes
 sor! Be sure to use academic language and question ideas from the readings
  for clarity or to push your own thinking.  You may of course respond to 
 more than two of the questions and more of your classmates if you would li
 ke.\n\n-------\nGRADING\n-------\n\nThis assignment is worth a total of 15
  points this is split into 10 points for a thoughtful post and 5 points fo
 r a thoughtful reply.  Once you post your answers to your selected quest
 ions\, you will be able to see your peer's responses. This discussion requ
 ires you to post first before seeing other responses. To see the specific 
 grading criteria for this assignment\, please [view the discussion rubric
 ] (https://community.canvaslms.com/docs/DOC-10577-4212540120).
