DESCRIPTION:[SYGN 502_What is Good Assignment_FA25.pdf] (https://elearning.
 mines.edu/courses/75170/files/8270432?wrap=1)\n\n \n\nWhat is Good? Assig
 nment\n\n \n\nDUE: On Canvas by class time (12pm) on October 6th\n\n \n\
 nPoints Value: 150 – 15% of overall grade\n\nMinimum 500 words\n\n \n\n
 Assignment: Conducting ethical research is important. But what constitutes
  ethical research and what is required to carry out this work can be diffe
 rent for different fields. With this assignment you are asked to explore w
 hat ethical research in your area of focus includes. This will mean seekin
 g information about what forms of guidance are available for your work suc
 h as codes of ethics\, regulatory requirements\, and relevant case example
 s or other educational resources.\n\n \n\nAdditionally\, in order to cond
 uct ethical research\, you must be able to do research. This often include
 s submitting research proposals\, applying for grant funding\, and getting
  institutional approval. Often\, there are certain field-specific aspects 
 of the research development process that include relevant ethical consider
 ations such as needing IRB approval for any human subjects research\, or n
 eeding to indicate data handling processes for research grant proposals.\n
 \n \n\nFor this assignment you will conduct a meaningful investigation of
  what Responsible Conduct of Research means in your field or area of speci
 fic research or professional destination.\n\n* You will then submit a shor
 t summary of what you discover including references to sources which provi
 de this guidance.\n\n* You should reflect on how you will integrate these 
 practices into your current and ongoing research and\n\n* Include some for
 m of personalized action plan or statement of intent.\n\n \n\nYou will be
  scored on the quality of your submission and its indication of the rigor 
 of your work.\n\n \n\nGeneral guidelines:\n\n C (70 points) ~ Something 
 turned in but it does not meet the requirements of the prompt\n\n* B (80 p
 oints) ~ Something turned in which does meet 500 word requirement and requ
 irements of the prompt but shows minimal input (is essentially a simple re
 flection piece)\n\n* A (90 points) ~ Meets all requirements of the prompt 
 and shows substantial research and integration of reflections and meaningf
 ul personalized action planning.\n\n* Full 100 points ~ Meets all of the a
 bove AND goes beyond with additional materials or demonstrated action take
 n (e.g.\, completing ethical steps of a research proposal or IRB-type subm
 ission)
