DESCRIPTION:Homework from Chapter 8.4 Exercises\n\n* Problems: 3\, 5\, 7\, 
 10a-g\, 12 (not including BART)\n\nIn this homework\, you will apply the r
 andom forest\, bagging\, and boosting approaches to datasets you have prev
 iously used\, with a more wide-ranging set of parameters to observe how th
 ese methods have the potential to improve upon the basic classification tr
 ees discussed initially. You will also answer some basic theoretical quest
 ions to improve your understanding of how these methods work.\n\nUse any t
 ypesetting software of your choice for the conceptual questions and use R 
 for all your analysis.\n\nHere is another friendly reminder that from modu
 le #3 onward your home works are done in teams of two. \n\nEstimated time
  to complete: 6 hours
