DESCRIPTION:Unit 3 Part 1 Progress\n\nIcon Progress Bar/Navigation (built i
 n browser\, hidden in app)\n\n \n\n----\nTASK\n----\n\nYour task for this
  discussion is to read the What is Machine Learning section in our Python 
 Data Science Handbook. You will then post a discussion and a reply below!
  \n\nReminder: The book is a reference guide and we have assigned the abo
 ve section as a reading on this topic at a high-level. Keep in mind\, it c
 ontains much more information than we cover in our course. As time permits
 \, you may find some interesting "extra" readings\, examples\, and informa
 tion.\n\n-----------------------\nDISCUSSION REQUIREMENTS\n---------------
 --------\n\nOnce you have completed this weeks reading\, you are asked to
  complete the following tasks:\n\n* Post a 1-2 sentence response from the 
 reading for 2 of the 3 below prompts:\n\n* Although there are several type
 s or categories of Machine Learning\, the book discusses two of the main c
 ategories of Machine Learning\, discuss your understanding of what they in
 volve and the primary differences?\n\n* There are four (4) different "Qual
 itative Examples of Machine Learning Applications" given\, provide a high-
 level understanding of each of these and select two you are most intereste
 d in to compare (or contrast) showing a deeper understanding. \n\n* Provi
 de a free response: this can be anything from clarification questions\, so
 mething that piqued your interest\, or may be a personal experience you ha
 ve with what was discussed in the book section.\n\n* Post a meaningful rep
 ly to another student's question/post. \n\nOur goal is to help you get a 
 deeper understanding of data science and discussions are a wonderful way t
 o do this! Think of this as a learning opportunity for both you\, your cla
 ssmates\, and your professor! Be sure to use academic language and questio
 n ideas from the readings for clarity or to push your own thinking.  You 
 may of course respond to more than two of the questions and more of your c
 lassmates if you would like.\n\n-------\nGRADING\n-------\n\nThis assignme
 nt is worth a total of 15 points this is split into 10 points for a though
 tful post and 5 points for a thoughtful reply.  Once you post your answe
 rs to your selected questions\, you will be able to see your peer's respon
 ses. This discussion requires you to post first before seeing other respon
 ses. To see the specific grading criteria for this assignment\, please [v
 iew the discussion rubric] (https://community.canvaslms.com/docs/DOC-10577
 -4212540120).
