 ataset for the project to implement an experiment in anomaly detection. Yo
 u can access the data from this file (<a class="instructure_file_link inli
 ne_disabled" title="creditcard.csv" href="https://elearning.mines.edu/cour
 ses/76742/files/8063759?wrap=1" target="_blank" data-api-endpoint="https:/
 /elearning.mines.edu/api/v1/courses/76742/files/8063759" data-api-returnty
 pe="File">creditcard.csv</a>).&nbsp\;</p>\n<p><strong>Dataset Description:
 </strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Real-World Dataset: The Credit Card Fraud Detecti
 on dataset which includes various features of transactions and a binary la
 bel indicating fraud.</li>\n<li>Note: If the dataset loading is slow / run
 ning crashes\, change your dataset to use a subset of the data.</li>\n</ul
 >\n<pre style="padding-left: 40px\;">df_subset = df[:1000]</pre>\n<h3>Data
  Preprocessing</h3>\n<p><strong>Loading Data: </strong>Load the Credit Car
 d Fraud Detection dataset using Pandas. Review the data using .info()\, .d
 escribe()\, etc.&nbsp\;</p>\n<p><strong>Handling Missing Values: </strong>
 Identify and handle any missing values in the dataset (e.g.\, using mean o
 r median imputation). This is KEY\, the GMM model cannot accept data with 
 missing data points.</p>\n<p><strong>Feature Scaling: </strong>Standardize
