 del's performance on unseen data.</p>\n<h3>Building the Model</h3>\n<p><st
 rong>Model Initialization:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Choosing Hyperparameter
 s: Explain key hyperparameters such as the number of convolutional layers\
 , filter sizes\, kernel sizes\, activation functions\, and dropout rates.<
 /li>\n<li>CNN Initialization: Use the TensorFlow and Keras libraries to de
 fine the CNN architecture.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Model Fitting: </strong
 >Fit the CNN model to the preprocessed Rock-Paper-Scissors dataset. Fit fo
 r ~10-20 epochs (you can do more but this may take extra time\, remember\,
  the training may take some time for such a complex model).</p>\n<h3>Evalu
 ating the Model</h3>\n<p><strong>Performance Metrics: </strong>Calculate m
 etrics such as accuracy\, precision\, recall\, F1 score\, and confusion ma
 trix to evaluate the model. These metrics provide insights into the model
 ’s predictive performance and its ability to generalize.</p>\n<hr style=
 "color: #92a2bd\; border: 1px solid\;">\n<h2 class="p1">SUBMITTING YOUR SO
 LUTION</h2>\n<p class="p1">Submit your notebook file. To submit your noteb
 ook\, first clear all the cells (this won't matter too much this time\, bu
 t for larger data sets in the future\, it will make the file smaller). The
 n use the File-&gt\;Download As-&gt\;Notebook to obtain the notebook file.
  Finally\, submit the notebook file(s) with your solutions to Canvas.</p><
