DESCRIPTION:Unit 4 Progress\n\nIcon Progress Bar/Navigation (built in brows
 er\, hidden in app)\n\n \n\n---------\nOBJECTIVE\n---------\n\nThe primar
 y objective of this project is to engage in deep-level thinking and apply 
 the concepts we've learned during the results and evaluation stage of our 
 workflow.\n\n------------\nINSTRUCTIONS\n------------\n\nSelect TWO (2) of
  your favorite projects\, each representing a different type of model we s
 tudied during the model selection portion of the class (e.g.\, one cluster
 ing and one instance-based).\n\n* Apply techniques for model evaluation an
 d parameter tuning to these projects. In the next section\, you will find 
 recommendations for each model.\n\n* For each model you selected\, provide
  a brief explanation at the bottom of the Jupyter Notebook File (about a p
 aragraph) detailing the techniques you used\, their impact on the solution
  (whether it improved or worsened)\, the parameters you tuned\, and your o
 verall thoughts on the performance.\n\n------------------\nSELECT YOUR MOD
 ELS\n------------------\n\nFor each model we have studied\, we have provid
 ed recommended activities for evaluating your model and tuning its hyperpa
 rameters/parameters. If you discover additional or alternative experiments
 \, feel free to include them in your analysis.\n\nLinear Regression\n-----
 ------------\n\nLinear Regression\n-----------------\n\nEvaluating the Mod
 el\n\n* Model Evaluation:\n\n* Performance Metrics: Calculate metrics such
  as Mean Absolute Error (MAE)\, Mean Squared Error (MSE)\, Root Mean Squar
 ed Error (RMSE)\, and R-squared (R2) to evaluate the model. These metrics 
