 erstand the model’s learning process.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Tuning Mod
 el Parameters</strong></p>\n<p>Hyperparameter Tuning: Use techniques such 
 as learning rate scheduling\, early stopping\, and model checkpointing to 
 systematically explore a range of hyperparameters for the CNN model and id
 entify the combination that results in the best performance.</p>\n<p><span
  style="text-decoration: underline\;"><strong>Specific Tuning Steps:</stro
 ng></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Define a range of learning rates:</p>\n</li
 >\n</ul>\n<pre style="padding-left: 40px\;">learning_rates = [0.001\, 0.00
 01\, 0.00001]</pre>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Implement early stopping to avoid over
 fitting:</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<pre style="padding-left: 40px\;">EarlyStoppin
 g(monitor='val_loss'\, patience=5)</pre>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Use model checkpo
 inting to save the best model:</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<pre style="padding-left
 : 40px\;">ModelCheckpoint(filepath='best_model.h5'\, monitor='val_loss'\, 
 save_best_only=True)</pre>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline\;">
 <strong>Download Sample Images for Predictions (optional):</strong></span>
 </p>\n<p><img class="instructure_file_link inline_disabled" src="https://e
 learning.mines.edu/courses/76742/files/8063843/download" alt="rock_sample"
  width="85" height="85" data-api-endpoint="https://elearning.mines.edu/api
 /v1/courses/76742/files/8063843" data-api-returntype="File" loading="lazy"
