DESCRIPTION:Unit 6 Progress\n\nIcon Progress Bar/Navigation (built in brows
 er\, hidden in app)\n\n \n\n----\nTASK\n----\n\nYour task for this discus
 sion is to read one (ore more) of the following sections on advanced topic
 s in visualizations in our Python Data Science Handbook. You will then pos
 t a discussion and a reply below! \n\n* Matplotlib:\n\n* Multiple Subplot
 s\n\n* Text and Annotation\n\n* Customizing Ticks\n\n* Customizing Matplot
 lib: Configurations and Stylesheets\n\n* Three-Dimensional Plotting in Mat
 plotlib\n\n* Visualization with Seaborn\n\n* Other Python Visualization Li
 braries\n\n* Bokeh\n\n* Plotly\n\nReminder: The book is a reference guide 
 and we have assigned the above section as a reading on this topic at a hig
 h-level. Keep in mind\, it contains much more information than we cover in
  our course. As time permits\, you may find some interesting "extra" readi
 ngs\, examples\, and information.\n\n-----------------------\nDISCUSSION R
 EQUIREMENTS\n-----------------------\n\nOnce you have completed this weeks
  reading\, you are asked to complete the following tasks:\n\n* Post a 1-2
  sentence response from the reading for 2 of the three below prompts:\n\n*
  Select a feature or idea that you would like to implement and a few sente
 nces about how that would add value to your data storytelling / reporting 
 of your final results.\n\n* Select a library you have not used in the past
  (e.g.\, seaborn\, bokeh\, plotly\, other) and discuss what benefits it wo
 uld have over that of the basic matplotlib.\n\n* Provide a free response: 
 this can be anything from clarification questions\, something that piqued 
 your interest\, or may be a personal experience you have with what was dis
 cussed in the book section.\n\n* Post a meaningful reply to another studen
 t's question/post. \n\nOur goal is to help you get a deeper understanding
  of data science and discussions are a wonderful way to do this! Think of 
 this as a learning opportunity for both you\, your classmates\, and your p
 rofessor! Be sure to use academic language and question ideas from the rea
 dings for clarity or to push your own thinking.  You may of course respon
 d to more than two of the questions and more of your classmates if you wou
 ld like.\n\n-------\nGRADING\n-------\n\nThis assignment is worth a total 
 of 15 points this is split into 10 points for a thoughtful post and 5 poin
 ts for a thoughtful reply.  Once you post your answers to your selected 
 questions\, you will be able to see your peer's responses. This discussion
  requires you to post first before seeing other responses. To see the spec
 ific grading criteria for this assignment\, please [view the discussion r
 ubric] (https://community.canvaslms.com/docs/DOC-10577-4212540120).
