X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://instructu
 re-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account_98020000000000001/attachments/7108468/
 dp_app3.css"><p><strong>Unit 6 Progress</strong></p>\n<p class="kl_module_
 progress_icons" style="display: none\;">Icon Progress Bar/Navigation (buil
 t in browser\, hidden in app)</p>\n<p>&nbsp\;</p>\n<h2>OBJECTIVE</h2>\n<p>
 The overall objective of this project is to package your work by applying 
 the concepts learned during the data storytelling and advanced visualizati
 on stages of our workflow.</p>\n<hr style="color: #92a2bd\; border: 1px so
 lid\;">\n<h2>INSTRUCTIONS</h2>\n<p>Select TWO (2) of your favorite project
 s\, each representing a different type of model we studied during the mode
 l selection portion of the class (e.g.\, one clustering and one instance-b
 ased). This can be new ones or the same projects selected in the <strong>R
 esults and Evaluation Project</strong>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Apply data storytel
 ling techniques\, including advanced or explanatory visualizations\, to th
 ese projects. In the next section\, you will find recommendations for visu
 alizations you can use for each model.</li>\n<li>For each model you select
 ed\, prepare a detailed report in the form of a Jupyter Notebook File (or 
 pdf report) summarizing the project\, including the following sections:\n<
 ul>\n<li><strong>Audience</strong>: Before starting you will need to choos
 e who your presentation will be aimed at. Please provide a paragraph that 
 details who the stakeholders are\, what they may know or not know and how 
 you will tailor your presentation to their needs. Some ideas are data scie
 ntist\, students\, managers\, C-suite executives\, general public\, etc.</
 li>\n<li><strong>Introduction</strong>: Provide a brief overview of the pr
 oblem and the chosen dataset.</li>\n<li><strong>Data Preprocessing</strong
 >: Describe the data preprocessing steps\, including loading\, data explor
 ation and visualization\, handling missing values\, encoding categorical v
 ariables\, feature engineering\, and standardizing the data.</li>\n<li><st
 rong>Model Architecture</strong>: Explain the model and the selected param
 eters.<br><strong></strong></li>\n<li><strong>Training and Evaluation</str
 ong>: Summarize the training process\, the evaluation metrics used\, and t
 he results obtained.</li>\n<li><strong>Parameter Tuning</strong>: Discuss 
 the experiments conducted to find the optimal hyperparameters and their ou
 tcomes.</li>\n<li><strong>Visualizations</strong> (see below for recommend
 ations for visualizations you can use for each model).</li>\n<li><strong>C
 onclusion</strong>: Share insights gained from the project and potential i
 mprovements for future work.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr style="color: 
 #92a2bd\; border: 1px solid\;">\n<h2>SELECT YOUR MODELS</h2>\n<p>For each 
 model we have studied\, we have provided recommended visualizations you ca
 n use. If you discover additional or alternative ideas\, feel free to incl
 ude them in your analysis.</p>\n<div id="kl_wrapper_3" class="kl_wrapper">
 \n<div id="kl_panel_block_0" class="">\n<div class="kl_panels_wrapper kl_p
 anels_tabs">\n<h3 id="kl_panel_0" class="kl_panel_heading kl_panel_0">Line
 ar Regression</h3>\n<div id="kl_panel_0_content" class="kl_panel_content k
 l_panel_0">\n<h3 class="kl_panel_heading kl_panel_0">Linear Regression</h3
 >\n<ul>\n<li>Residual Plot: Visualize the residual plot to understand the 
 model’s performance in detail\, including how well the model captures th
 e patterns in the data.</li>\n<li>Prediction Plot: Plot the predicted vs. 
 actual values to visualize how well the model predicts the target variable
 .</li>\n<li>Learning Curves: Plot learning curves to show the model’s pe
 rformance (e.g.\, MSE) as a function of the number of training samples. Th
 is helps in understanding how the model’s performance improves with more
  data.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h3 id="kl_panel_1" class="kl_panel_heading kl
 _panel_1">K-Nearest Neighbors</h3>\n<div id="kl_panel_1_content" class="kl
 _panel_content kl_panel_1">\n<h3 class="kl_panel_heading kl_panel_1">K-Nea
 rest Neighbors</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Confusion Matrix: Visualize the confusion m
 atrix to understand the model’s performance in detail\, including how ma
 ny instances were correctly or incorrectly classified for each class.</li>
 \n<li>Learning Curves: Plot learning curves to show the model’s performa
 nce (e.g.\, accuracy) as a function of the number of training samples. Thi
 s helps in understanding how the model’s performance improves with more 
 data.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h3 id="kl_panel_2" class="kl_panel_heading kl_
 panel_2">Support Vector Machines</h3>\n<div id="kl_panel_2_content" class=
 "kl_panel_content kl_panel_2">\n<h3 class="kl_panel_heading kl_panel_2">Su
 pport Vector Machines</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Confusion Matrix: Visualize the conf
 usion matrix to understand the model’s performance in detail\, including
  how many instances were correctly or incorrectly classified for each clas
 s.</li>\n<li>Decision Boundary: Visualize the decision boundary (if applic
 able) to understand how the SVM separates the different classes.</li>\n<li
 >Learning Curves: Plot learning curves to show the model’s performance (
 e.g.\, accuracy) as a function of the number of training samples. This hel
 ps in understanding how the model’s performance improves with more data.
  Using sklearn or another library:<br><a href="https://scikit-learn.org/st
 able/auto_examples/model_selection/plot_learning_curve.html" target="_blan
 k">https://scikit-learn.org/stable/auto_examples/model_selection/plot_lear
 ning_curve.html</a>&nbsp\;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h3 id="kl_panel_3" class=
 "kl_panel_heading kl_panel_3">Decision Trees</h3>\n<div id="kl_panel_3_con
 tent" class="kl_panel_content kl_panel_3">\n<h3>Decision Trees</h3>\n<ul>\
 n<li>Confusion Matrix: Visualize the confusion matrix to understand the mo
 del’s performance in detail\, including how many instances were correctl
 y or incorrectly classified for each class.</li>\n<li>Feature Importance P
 lot: Create a bar plot of feature importances to visualize which features 
 are most influential in the model’s predictions.</li>\n</ul>\n<pre style
 ="padding-left: 40px\;"># Feature importance for the base decision tree<br
 >importances = dt.feature_importances_<br>indices = np.argsort(importances
 )[::-1]<br>feature_names = df.columns[:-1]</pre>\n<ul>\n<li>Learning Curve
 s: Plot learning curves to show the model’s performance (e.g.\, accuracy
 ) as a function of the number of training samples. This helps in understan
 ding how the model’s performance improves with more data.</li>\n<li>Plot
  Best Tree: Using sklearn or another library\, plot the decision tree.<br>
 \n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/skl
 earn.tree.plot_tree.html" target="_blank">https://scikit-learn.org/stable/
 modules/generated/sklearn.tree.plot_tree.html</a>&nbsp\;</li>\n</ul>\n</li
 >\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h3 id="kl_panel_4" class="kl_panel_heading kl_panel_4">
 Random Forests</h3>\n<div id="kl_panel_4_content" class="kl_panel_content 
 kl_panel_4">\n<h3>Random Forests</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Confusion Matrix: Visuali
 ze the confusion matrix to understand the model’s performance in detail\
 , including how many instances were correctly or incorrectly classified fo
 r each class.</li>\n<li>Feature Importance Plot: Create a bar plot of feat
 ure importances to visualize which features are most influential in the mo
 del’s predictions.</li>\n</ul>\n<pre style="padding-left: 40px\;"># Get 
 feature importances<br>importances = rf.feature_importances_<br>indices = 
 np.argsort(importances)[::-1]<br>feature_names = df.columns[:-1]</pre>\n<u
 l>\n<li>Learning Curves: Plot learning curves to show the model’s perfor
 mance (e.g.\, accuracy) as a function of the number of training samples. T
 his helps in understanding how the model’s performance improves with mor
 e data.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h3 id="kl_panel_5" class="kl_panel_heading k
 l_panel_5">k-Means Clustering</h3>\n<div id="kl_panel_5_content" class="kl
 _panel_content kl_panel_5">\n<h3 class="kl_panel_heading kl_panel_5">k-Mea
 ns Clustering</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Scatter Plot: Create a scatter plot of the d
 ata points with colors indicating their cluster assignments. Highlight the
  cluster centroids on the plot.</li>\n<li>Pair Plot: For multi-dimensional
  data like the Iris dataset\, use pair plots to visualize the clustering r
 esults across different feature combinations.</li>\n<li>Centroids: Plot th
 e centroids of the clusters to show the center of each cluster.</li>\n<li>
 Sources: <a href="https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklear
 n.cluster.KMeans.html" target="_blank">https://scikit-learn.org/stable/mod
 ules/generated/sklearn.cluster.KMeans.html</a>&nbsp\;<strong></strong><str
 ong></strong></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h3 id="kl_panel_6" class="kl_panel_hea
 ding kl_panel_6">Gaussian Mixture Model</h3>\n<div id="kl_panel_6_content"
  class="kl_panel_content kl_panel_6">\n<h3 class="kl_panel_heading kl_pane
 l_6">Gaussian Mixture Model</h3>\n<p>Anomaly Detection Visualization:</p>\
 n<ul>\n<li>Real-World Data: Plot the distribution of anomaly scores and vi
 sualize the detected anomalies.</li>\n<li>Visualize the clusters and their
  distributions using scatter plots and contour plots.<strong></strong></li
 >\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h3 id="kl_panel_7" class="kl_panel_heading kl_panel_7">
 Artificial Neural Networks</h3>\n<div id="kl_panel_7_content" class="kl_pa
 nel_content kl_panel_7">\n<h3 class="kl_panel_heading kl_panel_7">Artifici
 al Neural Networks</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Accuracy/Loss Plots: Plot the training 
 and validation accuracy/loss over epochs to visualize the model's learning
  process.</li>\n<li>Interpretation: Analyze the plots to understand the mo
 del's behavior (e.g.\, detecting overfitting\, underfitting).</li>\n</ul>\
 n</div>\n<h3 id="kl_panel_8" class="kl_panel_heading kl_panel_8">Convoluti
 onal Neural Networks</h3>\n<div id="kl_panel_8_content" class="kl_panel_co
 ntent kl_panel_8">\n<h3 class="kl_panel_heading kl_panel_8">Convolutional 
 Neural Networks</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Confusion Matrix: Visualize the confusion 
 matrix to understand the model’s performance in detail\, including how m
 any instances were correctly or incorrectly classified for each class.</li
 >\n<li>Loss and Accuracy Curves: Plot the loss and accuracy curves to visu
 alize the model’s training process and detect any signs of overfitting o
 r underfitting.<strong><br></strong></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n
 </div>\n<hr style="color: #92a2bd\; border: 1px solid\;">\n<h2 class="p1">
 SUBMITTING YOUR SOLUTION</h2>\n<p class="p1">Submit your notebook file(s) 
 or pdf(s). To submit your notebook\, first clear all the cells (this won't
  matter too much this time\, but for larger data sets in the future\, it w
 ill make the file smaller). Then use the File-&gt\;Download As-&gt\;Notebo
 ok to obtain the notebook file. Finally\, submit the notebook file(s) with
  your solutions to Canvas.</p><script src="https://instructure-uploads.s3.
 amazonaws.com/account_98020000000000001/attachments/7108467/dp_app%20%2528
 1%2529.js"></script>
END:VEVENT
