  applied data science project: it is critical to think about the potential
  societal and ethical implications of your work. \n\nBe sure you have rev
 iewed the [Applied Data Science Project Introduction.] (https://elearning
 .mines.edu/courses/76742/pages/applied-data-science-project-introduction)\
 n\nOverview: Provide a thorough discussion of the ethical implications ass
 ociated with your work\, considering any potential impacts on privacy\, bi
 as\, and fairness. Address how your data collection\, analysis\, and model
  development processes adhere to ethical standards and guidelines. Additio
 nally\, identify and discuss any limitations of your project\, such as con
 straints related to data quality\, model assumptions\, or generalizability
  of your results. This section should demonstrate your awareness of the br
 oader context of your work and your ability to critically assess the poten
 tial ethical concerns and limitations that may affect the validity and app
 licability of your findings.\n\nTo see the specific grading criteria for t
 his assignment\, please view the rubric.
